Sentencas: Two-cell arrayed integrated planar solid oxide fuel cells (IP-SOFCs) were fabricated using a robo-dispensing method.
Titulo: Influence of reduced substrate shunting current on cell performance in integrated planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Special emphasis was placed on the influence of reduced shunting current on cell performance.
Titulo: Influence of reduced substrate shunting current on cell performance in integrated planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The resistivity of the substrate increased according to a mixture rule of composites by adding Al(2)O(3) into the substrate of partially stabilized zirconia (PSZ).
Titulo: Influence of reduced substrate shunting current on cell performance in integrated planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This strategy, which reduces shunting current through the substrate, enhances the power output.
Titulo: Influence of reduced substrate shunting current on cell performance in integrated planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: When the amount of Al(2)O(3) added was more than 26 vol%, however, the Ni anode migrated into the PSZ substrate to react with Al(2)O(3), which led to performance degradation.
Titulo: Influence of reduced substrate shunting current on cell performance in integrated planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In the case of the two-cell arrayed IP-SOFC with a 20 vol%-Al(2)O(3) added to the PSZ substrate, a reduced shunting current loss improved the power density by 30% compared to that of the Al(2)O(3)-free substrate.
Titulo: Influence of reduced substrate shunting current on cell performance in integrated planar solid oxide fuel cells
